# Seldon (Agent Review + UI work)

## Agent Review

When running **Cursor Agent Review**, **PR review**, or any **automated code
review** on this repository, you **must** treat the following as binding project
standards (not suggestions):

1. **Canonical skill:** Read and apply **`.agents/skills/seldon/SKILL.md`**
   (Seldon skill): library scope, co-located stories and tests, SCSS + `px` / `$px`
   conventions.
2. **Repo rules:** **`AGENTS.md`**, **`docs/agents/CONVENTIONS.md`**,
   **`docs/agents/QUALITY.md`**.
3. **Checklist:** **`.cursor/commands/code-review-checklist.md`** — verify
   Storybook/tests where applicable, accessibility, and BEM / prefix rules.

Flag gaps explicitly (for example a new visual component without `.stories.tsx` /
`.test.tsx` when the rest of the folder uses that pattern).

## Everyday UI work

For edits under **`src/components/`** or **`src/patterns/`**, follow the same
**`.agents/skills/seldon/SKILL.md`** before merge. After substantive edits,
run **`npm run format`**.

## Cursor subagents (structured audits)

For **gap analysis** (not a substitute for CI), invoke or @mention these
**`.cursor/agents/`** definitions:

| Subagent                        | File                                            | Purpose                                                                          |
| ------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **component-unit-test-checker** | `.cursor/agents/component-unit-test-checker.md` | Flag `src/components/**` folders missing co-located `*.test.tsx` where expected. |
| **component-storybook-checker** | `.cursor/agents/component-storybook-checker.md` | Flag `src/components/**` missing co-located `*.stories.tsx` where expected.      |

Agent Review may **delegate** to these when verifying Seldon skill test and story
expectations.
